-- Boeing says it is ready to test 787-9 as early as Tuesday
-- 
-- Fri Sep 13, 2013 6:20pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/09/13/us-boeing-dreamliner-idUSBRE98C10F20130913

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Boeing Co's ( BA.N ) high-tech Dreamliner 787-9 aircraft will make its first flight as soon as Tuesday, the company said on Friday. 
 The flight-testing schedule may change due to weather conditions or other factors, the company said. Reuters reported on Thursday that the test flight was planned for next week. (Reporting by  Alwyn Scott ; writing by  Lauren Tara LaCapra ; Editing by  Bernard Orr )